<h1>Problem 186 - 2015 Saint Petersburg MO Grade 11, Q7 of 7, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(BL\) be the angle bisector of acute triangle \(ABC\), with \(L\) on \(AC\). Point \(K\) is chosen on \(BL\) such that \(\angle AKC - \angle ABC = 90^{\circ}\). Point \(S\) lies on the extension of \(BL\) from \(L\) such that \(\angle ASC = 90^{\circ}\). Point \(T\) is diametrically opposite the point \(K\) on the circumcircle of \(\triangle AKC\).</p>
<p>Prove that \(ST\) and the perpendicular bisector of \(AC\) concur on the circumcircle of \(ABC\).</p>
